
[1]gentian

   GEN'TIAN, n. [L. gentiana.] A genus of plants, of many species. The
   common gentian is a native of the mountainous parts of Germany. The
   root,the only part used, has a yellowish brown color and a very bitter
   taste, and is used as an ingredient in stomachic bitters. It is
   sometimes called felwort.
